-- Vale Plans $11.3 Billion Iron-Ore Mine in Northern Brazil, IG News Reports
-- Francisco Marcelino
-- 2010-07-26T12:02:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/vale-plans-11-3-billion-iron-ore-mine-in-northern-brazil-ig-news-reports.html

          
          
             Vale SA  plans to invest $11.3
billion in an iron-ore mine in northern Brazil,  IG reported ,
without saying where it obtained the information.  
 The mine, scheduled to begin operating in 2013, will have
capacity to produce 90 million metric tons a year of the
steelmaking raw material, the Sao Paulo-based news service said.  
 The mine will be located in the same region Vale operates
Carajas, the worldâ€™s largest iron-ore mine, IG said.  
